WEBVTT

01:09.361 --> 01:11.821
RAY:
Just because we've lost...

01:11.989 --> 01:14.949
...just because the past is not
what we wanted it to be...

01:15.117 --> 01:18.661
...does not mean we cannot change.

01:19.037 --> 01:20.413
In an instant, we could.

01:20.581 --> 01:21.581
[CROWD CHEERING]

01:21.749 --> 01:25.209
What do you wanna think tonight
when you replay this in your head...

01:25.377 --> 01:27.962
...with the lights out, trying to sleep?

01:28.130 --> 01:29.172
[WHISTLE BLOWS]

01:35.387 --> 01:38.681
JEMMA: I'm sorry I'm late.
- No problem.

01:38.849 --> 01:41.768
- Nice scarf.
- Oh, really? You like it?

01:41.935 --> 01:45.104
- Looks good on you.
- Thanks.

01:45.481 --> 01:47.690
- You ready?
- Yeah.

01:48.233 --> 01:51.027
- What are we doing?
- Don't ask me that.

01:51.904 --> 01:55.198
- Okay.
- You nervous?

01:55.365 --> 01:56.574
Um...

01:56.742 --> 01:58.701
Should I be?

02:00.037 --> 02:02.330
Yes, I'm nervous.

02:02.706 --> 02:05.416
Well, don't be. Come on.

02:08.212 --> 02:09.712
Thank you for coming, Jim.

02:12.883 --> 02:16.594
It's okay to feel a little uneasy.

02:16.762 --> 02:18.721
This must be difficult for you.

02:19.765 --> 02:23.226
- It means a lot to me that he's here.
- Of course it does.

02:23.560 --> 02:27.313
It does mean a lot, because you have to
understand I'm gonna confront you...

02:27.481 --> 02:30.608
...and most men would run from that,
so thanks for being here.

02:32.569 --> 02:34.570
You're welcome.

02:39.660 --> 02:43.287
- So what did you wanna confront?
- Should I just jump in here?

02:43.455 --> 02:47.250
- If you want to.
- I want to say to you, Jim, that...

02:48.085 --> 02:51.128
That your money destroys you.
Your father's money. L...

02:51.296 --> 02:54.924
It's like you're...
It's like you're choking on his vomit.

02:55.092 --> 02:58.928
It makes me wanna weep because
sometimes I picture you without him...

02:59.096 --> 03:00.847
...and his money, and the money...

03:01.014 --> 03:04.100
...and you're a completely different
human being.

03:07.563 --> 03:10.439
You don't do what you did, Jim.

03:10.816 --> 03:15.486
Not to me, not to anyone. You just...

03:16.154 --> 03:18.030
You just don't.

03:22.119 --> 03:24.287
I don't know what to do with him.

03:24.454 --> 03:26.831
He's like a stone wall.
I don't... Why did he even...?

03:26.999 --> 03:28.791
Why did he even agree to come here?

03:33.046 --> 03:36.966
- Do you...? Does she wanna...?
JEMMA: Don't talk to him. Talk to me.

03:37.926 --> 03:39.427
Explain to me why it happened.

03:39.595 --> 03:42.305
Maybe you went for
the wrong kind of guy.

03:42.472 --> 03:44.473
- Just tell me, for fuck's sake.
RAY: Jemma.

03:45.851 --> 03:49.896
- Swear the fuck out!
- I don't know why!

03:50.063 --> 03:56.527
Jemma, I don't know why things happen
in my life or your life.

03:57.112 --> 04:02.325
If I had to take a guess, I'd say,
something about you is a big, fat turnoff.

04:02.492 --> 04:04.327
Oh, like now?

04:05.245 --> 04:07.163
Am I a turnoff right now?

04:07.331 --> 04:09.165
No.

04:22.220 --> 04:24.347
RAY: Hey.
- Hey.

04:25.933 --> 04:29.685
- You okay?
- Yeah, I'm fine.

04:30.646 --> 04:33.356
So, what was that about, exactly?

04:33.523 --> 04:35.358
It doesn't matter.

04:38.070 --> 04:39.904
That's it?

04:40.072 --> 04:43.366
- What am I supposed to do now?
- I don't care what you do.

04:48.830 --> 04:50.456
- Jemma paid me.
- Paid you?

04:50.624 --> 04:53.292
Yeah, your cut's in my desk.
Don't worry, I locked it.

04:53.794 --> 04:55.962
- Paid you? For what?
- It's a long story.

04:56.129 --> 04:58.965
- She booked me for a session.
- When?

04:59.132 --> 05:01.008
It's over already. Just now.

05:01.176 --> 05:03.594
I saw her on my lunch break.

05:03.762 --> 05:07.473
She called me late last night.
What was I supposed to do?

05:07.641 --> 05:10.726
If a client calls you directly,
you tell me immediately.

05:10.894 --> 05:12.728
It's not cool. There's a protocol.

05:12.896 --> 05:15.231
She paid me $500.
What wrong with that?

05:15.399 --> 05:17.566
Last week you went to her house
behind my back.

05:17.734 --> 05:19.485
Now she's calling you at all hours.

05:19.653 --> 05:21.862
- A decent hour.
- I'm gonna have a talk with her.

05:22.030 --> 05:24.407
- Don't. That's not a good idea.
- Why not?

05:24.574 --> 05:26.575
She's... She's having a hard time.

05:27.077 --> 05:29.203
And you know this because?

05:29.371 --> 05:31.288
She took me to see her therapist.

05:32.082 --> 05:34.250
Yeah. I think that's why she hired me.

05:34.418 --> 05:37.044
I think I'm supposed to help her,
you know...

05:37.212 --> 05:39.714
...work shit out.
- A million things come to mind.

05:39.881 --> 05:42.508
I'm not gonna say them.
I'm just gonna keep my mouth shut.

05:42.676 --> 05:43.926
Leave her alone, okay?

05:44.094 --> 05:45.094
[CLASS BELL RINGS]

05:45.262 --> 05:47.013
I'll talk to her about the rules.

05:47.180 --> 05:49.640
- Okay.
- I gotta go.

05:56.314 --> 05:59.483
- Are you drinking enough water lately?
- What?

05:59.651 --> 06:01.527
You look dehydrated.

06:01.695 --> 06:03.946
What's that?
Some kind of dermatology putdown?

06:04.322 --> 06:07.616
No, baby, water's excellent for the skin.

06:07.784 --> 06:10.327
Yup. It's also good for depression.

06:10.620 --> 06:13.706
You lost your dog, he died,
and that's rough.

06:13.874 --> 06:16.042
I'm sick of water, Ron.

06:16.752 --> 06:18.794
I wanna talk about money.

06:18.962 --> 06:20.838
- What about it?
- Do we have it?

06:21.006 --> 06:23.382
Are we rich or are we poor? I can't tell.

06:23.550 --> 06:25.843
We drive a Mercedes
and we pay for Natasha.

06:26.011 --> 06:29.472
And on the other hand, Doris is dead.

06:29.639 --> 06:34.477
Well, we're not rich or poor, Jess,
but we did lose a lot.

06:34.644 --> 06:36.353
Thirty percent.

06:36.521 --> 06:38.439
- Maybe 40, so...
- Forty percent?

06:38.607 --> 06:42.443
- Yeah. I gotta get to the office.
- Forty percent of what, Ron?

06:42.611 --> 06:47.615
This is what is so frustrating, Ron.
You don't tell me anything.

06:48.116 --> 06:50.493
Is there something you wanna buy?

06:50.869 --> 06:53.662
Is there? Are you feeling neglected?
You feeling deprived?

06:53.830 --> 06:56.415
Because say the word, I'll buy it.

06:56.583 --> 07:00.878
You know, and if I can't afford it,
I'll hock my Jaeger, I'll wash dishes.

07:01.046 --> 07:04.298
- I'll eat hot coals for you, baby.
- I don't want you to eat hot coals.

07:04.466 --> 07:09.095
I just need to know the numbers.

07:09.262 --> 07:11.597
I don't know the exact numbers, Jess.

07:11.765 --> 07:16.143
But if you wanna help, you can make a list
of potential household cutbacks.

07:17.062 --> 07:19.355
Or you could always get a job.

07:30.742 --> 07:33.285
JEMMA: I still haven't heard anything,
so good luck with that.

07:34.371 --> 07:37.081
Hey. Hi. Thanks for meeting me here.

07:37.249 --> 07:40.042
- What?
- I left you a message about us meeting.

07:40.210 --> 07:42.878
You guys go ahead. I'll catch up.

07:43.213 --> 07:46.549
- What are you doing here?
- I know you're busy. You haven't called me.

07:46.716 --> 07:51.095
- I was in the neighborhood, so I thought...
- Terry, I'm working.

07:51.263 --> 07:52.888
- This is my place of work.
- Tanya.

07:53.056 --> 07:54.890
Why don't you tell me why you're here.

07:55.058 --> 07:58.769
Listen, Jemma, I thought I made myself
pretty clear in our initial interview.

07:58.937 --> 08:01.564
Now, what you wanted
was a little unorthodox.

08:01.731 --> 08:03.732
And I said,
"As long as you respect our rules."

08:03.900 --> 08:04.984
[PHONE RINGING]

08:05.152 --> 08:08.195
And one of those rules is
you do not contact or pay a client directly.

08:08.363 --> 08:12.533
Hold on. Hey, yeah.
Yeah, I'll be right there.

08:14.661 --> 08:16.245
Don't let him see it, Brad.

08:16.413 --> 08:18.706
It's pretty simple what...

08:18.874 --> 08:22.418
So that's the way it goes and,
you know, I know, as a businesswoman...

08:22.586 --> 08:25.504
...you understand after years of working
that there are certain systems...

08:25.672 --> 08:26.672
[PHONE RINGING]

08:26.840 --> 08:29.300
...that keep the trains running on time,
that you wanna have...

08:29.467 --> 08:30.509
I will be right up.

08:31.178 --> 08:33.512
L... What are you talking about?

08:33.680 --> 08:35.556
Our parameters.

08:35.724 --> 08:38.642
What if I just ignore you
and do whatever I want?

08:38.810 --> 08:40.603
What?

08:40.770 --> 08:45.482
What's stopping me from, I don't know,
just not bothering to listen to you?

08:47.319 --> 08:49.945
Well, I would stop you. It's my service.

08:50.113 --> 08:52.615
I'm the one who makes the rules.

08:52.782 --> 08:55.451
Jemma? Jemma.
I do not suffer fools gladly.

08:55.619 --> 08:58.037
Now, look, Ray... Ray is my employee.

08:58.205 --> 09:01.040
Now, you cannot get to him
except through me.

09:01.208 --> 09:02.625
We are inextricably linked.

09:03.376 --> 09:06.003
Who's Ray? You mean Randall?

09:06.796 --> 09:10.758
No, I do not mean Randall.
I mean, there is no Ray.

09:10.926 --> 09:14.303
You know what? You're fired.
That's right. I'm firing you as a client.

09:14.471 --> 09:17.389
You know, I've had enough of you
and women like you.

09:17.557 --> 09:19.516
Good riddance.

09:21.269 --> 09:22.561
[SIGHS]

09:26.650 --> 09:29.526
It's pretty good, huh?
I mean, check out the new panel.

09:29.694 --> 09:32.696
- It still smells a little wonky, though.
- That's normal.

09:32.864 --> 09:36.909
Anyway, I'll fix it
before we move you guys back in.

09:37.869 --> 09:39.328
- Cool.
- Great.

09:39.496 --> 09:41.538
Let's choose some wheels.

09:42.374 --> 09:44.583
All right. I circled the ones
I think are good.

09:44.751 --> 09:47.169
You tell me which one's got
your name on it.

09:47.629 --> 09:49.922
- An '89 Mustang?
- Yeah, vintage.

09:50.090 --> 09:52.841
It says so right there in the ad.
Heck of a car.

09:53.009 --> 09:55.344
It's got 120,000 miles.

09:55.512 --> 09:58.514
So? Those are highway miles.

09:58.682 --> 10:00.224
I talked to the guy selling it.

10:00.392 --> 10:01.558
[PHONE RINGING]

10:01.726 --> 10:03.602
All right, whatever. You guys decide.

10:04.187 --> 10:06.563
Where are you going?
I thought we were buying a car.

10:06.731 --> 10:08.440
She doesn't give a shit, Dad.

10:08.608 --> 10:11.193
All she cares about
is her fat-ass boyfriend.

10:11.361 --> 10:13.070
Hey, hey, give it a rest, Damon.

10:13.238 --> 10:15.864
Maybe she sees something you don't.

10:16.700 --> 10:19.451
- What are you talking about?
- I'm saying people are complex.

10:19.619 --> 10:21.412
They're like...

10:21.579 --> 10:23.455
...onions.

10:23.873 --> 10:29.211
You peel a layer and sometimes you find
something that you weren't expecting.

10:30.046 --> 10:33.716
No, you don't. You just find more onion.

10:34.884 --> 10:38.012
[TANYA SPEAKING SPANISH]

10:41.683 --> 10:45.060
TANYA: Holy cow, Ray,
this place is really coming along.

10:45.854 --> 10:48.731
It still really smells though.

10:48.898 --> 10:52.401
Oh. Uh... So is this your...?

10:52.569 --> 10:54.903
- Hi.
- Hi. You must be Ray's...

10:55.071 --> 10:56.739
Yeah, Tanya, this is my kid.

10:57.574 --> 10:59.992
Damon, Tanya.

11:00.160 --> 11:01.618
Hi. Wow.

11:01.786 --> 11:03.620
I think I see the resemblance.

11:03.788 --> 11:07.333
- Yeah. The eyebrows, right?
- Damon, we'll be right back.

11:07.500 --> 11:11.587
Take a look at the '89 Mustang, huh?
You can use this time to get excited.

11:11.755 --> 11:14.173
- Nice meeting you.
- Oh, yeah, you too.

11:14.341 --> 11:16.842
Thanks, Tanya. Now my kid thinks
you're my girlfriend.

11:17.010 --> 11:20.012
TANYA: What? Just because I show up
at your house? Don't be infantile.

11:20.180 --> 11:21.847
- What do you want?
- I got great news.

11:22.015 --> 11:25.309
I caught up with Molly and
she wants to book you again for Saturday.

11:25.477 --> 11:28.312
- This Saturday?
- Yeah, you can go on the early side...

11:28.480 --> 11:31.273
...and then come over and meet me
and download after.

11:31.441 --> 11:35.444
I got a bunch of Netflix films.
I'll pop some popcorn, you can come over.

11:35.612 --> 11:37.988
No, Tanya, I got a life.
I got a game this Saturday.

11:38.156 --> 11:40.366
Okay, so maybe we'll make it Friday then.

11:40.533 --> 11:42.618
No, Jemma mentioned she wanted Friday.

11:42.786 --> 11:45.871
Don't worry. I'll make her book
through you.

11:46.748 --> 11:49.666
Okay, it's too late for that.

11:50.293 --> 11:51.960
I made an executive decision.

11:52.879 --> 11:56.465
What are you talking about?
I'm an executive too. She's fine.

11:56.633 --> 11:59.635
No, she's rude and I fired her.

11:59.803 --> 12:02.888
I fired her. I lost my temper. I fired her.

12:03.056 --> 12:05.015
Well, unfire her.

12:05.183 --> 12:07.518
Jeez, Tanya.
Why'd you have to go mess this up for?

12:07.685 --> 12:11.230
I'm not messing this up.

12:12.482 --> 12:15.484
I'm fixing it, okay? I'll fix it.

12:15.652 --> 12:18.070
L... l... Just leave me alone.

12:20.573 --> 12:23.200
JESSICA:
Mom, I do not feel comfortable with this.

12:23.368 --> 12:25.994
Ronnie's a private person.
I wanna respect his privacy.

12:26.162 --> 12:28.622
- So? You go.
- What about you?

12:28.790 --> 12:30.999
I stay and not respects privacy.

12:32.419 --> 12:35.212
Look, credit card bills.

12:35.380 --> 12:39.675
Visa, MasterCard, more Visa.

12:39.843 --> 12:42.678
- What does it prove?
- Poor people don't spend so much.

12:42.846 --> 12:45.514
Only rich ones.

12:46.099 --> 12:47.683
Make sure you put everything back.

12:47.851 --> 12:50.602
- He's gonna notice if things are disturbed.
- You are wife.

12:50.770 --> 12:52.855
You have right to know
when husband is liar.

12:53.022 --> 12:56.233
- He's not a liar, mother.
- He is worse than liar.

12:56.401 --> 12:59.903
Treats you like child. Worse than child.

13:00.071 --> 13:02.197
He treats you like pet.

13:02.782 --> 13:04.366
Like your dead dog.

13:04.784 --> 13:06.201
What are you talking about?

13:06.369 --> 13:09.037
You want little needle in your face?

13:09.205 --> 13:11.290
Too much wrinkle here,
too much pimple there.

13:11.458 --> 13:14.209
He takes care of me, Mother.
He takes care of you.

13:14.377 --> 13:16.545
How much money he has? Do you know?

13:16.713 --> 13:21.049
Of course not,
because he doesn't want you to know.

13:21.217 --> 13:24.052
That's enough. You're driving me crazy.
Put it away.

13:25.597 --> 13:28.557
Aha. Stock exchange.

13:28.725 --> 13:31.894
I find the most important file.

13:32.479 --> 13:34.897
Now you tell me he's not rich.

13:35.064 --> 13:38.567
Eight hundred and
thirty-three thousand dollars.

13:42.405 --> 13:44.323
Why is it in parentheses?

13:45.658 --> 13:48.744
It's a loss, Mom.

13:50.705 --> 13:55.083
It means he lost $833,000.

13:58.755 --> 14:01.757
Okay, so maybe I wrong.
Maybe he lost money.

14:02.842 --> 14:06.094
You hungry? I make something to eat.

14:06.429 --> 14:09.973
JEMMA [ON RECORDING]: This is Jemma.
Be patient, you'll get an answer eventually.

14:10.141 --> 14:13.435
No. Hey, Jemma, it's Tanya.

14:13.603 --> 14:15.604
Listen, I've got some terrific news.

14:15.772 --> 14:19.566
Despite our previous miscommunication,
I had a discussion with Randall...

14:19.734 --> 14:23.612
...and we've decided to allow you
to keep your membership...

14:24.822 --> 14:28.534
...provided you respect our rules.

14:28.868 --> 14:33.497
Just please give me a call
at your convenience. Okay.

14:38.378 --> 14:39.711
You should call her back.

14:39.879 --> 14:42.172
I'm sorry. I've been swamped.

14:42.340 --> 14:47.511
But really, Randall, all that talk
about regulations and parameters?

14:47.679 --> 14:50.013
She is a trip, your Tanya.

14:50.181 --> 14:54.518
- She's not my Tanya.
- Well, she's your madam, isn't she?

14:56.312 --> 14:57.980
I thought I was a book editor.

14:58.147 --> 15:00.148
Oh, book editor.

15:01.484 --> 15:02.568
That's so yesterday.

15:05.071 --> 15:06.863
What's your real name?

15:11.786 --> 15:14.329
RAY: I can't tell you that.
- Why not?

15:14.497 --> 15:16.582
Take a leap of faith.

15:17.208 --> 15:21.211
And if you can't, just make something up.
I'm not gonna know the difference.

15:25.508 --> 15:27.551
My name is Ray.

15:29.429 --> 15:31.096
More.

15:31.264 --> 15:32.389
- Tell me more.
- No.

15:32.557 --> 15:33.974
- Please?
- No.

15:34.142 --> 15:37.519
I'll pay you, lots.

15:37.687 --> 15:39.646
- What do you think I am, a whore?
- Yeah.

15:39.814 --> 15:40.814
[LAUGHS]

15:40.982 --> 15:42.190
Yes, you're a whore.

15:43.276 --> 15:47.863
You're so funny and you're so hot
and I'm very into you.

15:48.031 --> 15:50.198
But you're gonna tell me.

15:54.245 --> 15:56.038
Is this all you do?

15:58.833 --> 16:01.460
- Are you a fireman?
- No.

16:01.628 --> 16:04.546
- Policeman?
- No.

16:04.714 --> 16:06.715
- A plumber?
- No.

16:06.883 --> 16:08.383
Stop torturing me.

16:09.427 --> 16:10.719
No.

16:10.887 --> 16:13.221
You're making me wanna fuck you.

16:13.556 --> 16:16.058
I'm gonna charge you double.

16:16.225 --> 16:19.353
Tell me what you fucking do for a living.

16:21.356 --> 16:23.398
I'm a coach.

16:23.900 --> 16:28.570
I'm a high school basketball coach.

16:28.821 --> 16:31.239
I wanna see you do it.

16:31.407 --> 16:34.076
I mean, coach.

16:34.243 --> 16:35.619
[INSTRUMENTAL MUSIC PLAYING ON TV]

16:36.663 --> 16:38.955
Oh, no.

17:01.771 --> 17:03.271
[WHISTLE BLOWS]

17:05.692 --> 17:09.528
Come on, defense. Come on.

17:11.114 --> 17:12.447
[CROWD BOOING]

17:13.950 --> 17:16.326
RAY:
It was looking like another losing game.

17:16.494 --> 17:20.163
So many teams were having us for lunch,
I barely remembered how to win.

17:20.331 --> 17:21.748
[WHISTLE BLOWS & CROWD BOOING]

17:21.916 --> 17:23.709
REFEREE: Foul.
- He didn't touch him.

17:23.876 --> 17:26.294
RAY:
Come on, ref. Call it both ways.

17:26.462 --> 17:29.005
This ref's making bogus calls all night.

17:30.258 --> 17:32.092
[CROWD BOOING]

17:32.260 --> 17:34.886
What are you looking at, Ray, huh?

17:35.054 --> 17:37.472
- Yeah.
- Get your head in the game.

17:39.976 --> 17:41.143
[CROWD BOOING]

17:41.310 --> 17:42.769
ANNOUNCER [ON PA]:
And that's the half.

17:42.937 --> 17:48.024
The score: Wolves 26,
Tomahawks 36.

17:48.192 --> 17:50.777
Oh, my God, I love that lip gloss.
Where did you get it?

17:50.945 --> 17:54.364
Hi, can I have one ticket
for the Wolves and two buttons?

17:54.532 --> 17:58.535
- You mean the game.
- Right, the game.

17:58.703 --> 18:00.162
- Thank you.
- Hey.

18:00.872 --> 18:03.749
Oh, hey. Hi. Damon, right?

18:03.916 --> 18:06.668
- How are you?
- I'm good.

18:06.836 --> 18:08.044
ALL:
Fight, Wolves, fight.

18:08.212 --> 18:11.465
Are you a...? Do you...?
Do you go to the games?

18:11.632 --> 18:14.760
Me? Oh, no, no. I just...
I was home, having a moody night...

18:14.927 --> 18:17.137
...so I thought I should be around
human beings.

18:18.306 --> 18:22.601
Yeah, well, there's human beings here,
I guess.

18:22.769 --> 18:25.187
- If you kind of like that.
- You're funny, aren't you?

18:25.688 --> 18:30.692
Yeah. I guess l... I guess I kind of have,
like, a funny personality.

18:31.527 --> 18:33.779
JESSICA: Oh, hey, sweetie. You ready?
DAMON: Hi.

18:34.363 --> 18:38.366
Mom, this is a friend of Dad's.

18:38.743 --> 18:43.330
- Oh, wow. A friend of Dad's. I'm Jessica.
- Hi.

18:43.498 --> 18:45.749
- Tanya. Nice to meet you.
- Nice to meet you.

18:45.917 --> 18:48.126
Yeah. You're Darby, right?

18:48.294 --> 18:51.546
- Yeah.
- Great.

18:51.964 --> 18:53.590
Well...

18:53.758 --> 18:55.717
- So let's get back to the game, huh?
- Yeah.

18:55.885 --> 18:59.805
- Where are you sitting?
- Me? I don't know. Anywhere. I don't know.

18:59.972 --> 19:03.683
- Fifty-one is killing us out there.
- Yeah.

19:06.395 --> 19:09.898
RAY: I knew I should have paid more
attention. My heart just wasn't in it.

19:10.066 --> 19:13.235
Pazderka, box his ass out, okay?
This is varsity. Come on.

19:13.402 --> 19:14.569
TANYA:
Whoo!

19:14.737 --> 19:17.113
RAY:
In two years, no one came to my games.

19:17.281 --> 19:22.160
Now here we were
in the worst losing streak of my life...

19:22.328 --> 19:26.289
...and my ex-wife, my two kids
and my pimp...

19:26.457 --> 19:28.917
...were all sitting up there, side by side.

19:29.085 --> 19:31.545
MIKE: Guys, let's go. Come on.
- Get them up. Yeah.

19:31.712 --> 19:35.423
What's wrong with Dad?
He seems kind of out of it.

19:35.591 --> 19:36.925
JESSICA:
Oh, I don't know.

19:37.093 --> 19:40.387
- Has he been putting on weight?
- Oh, I think he lost weight.

19:41.097 --> 19:42.848
Must be all that camping.

19:43.015 --> 19:46.268
DARBY: Do you have any idea
how much of an idiot you are?

19:46.435 --> 19:48.603
I mean, you don't even have
a personality.

19:48.771 --> 19:50.856
- I do too have a personality.
- No, you don't.

19:51.023 --> 19:52.941
Even the goth kids think you're a poseur.

19:53.109 --> 19:56.278
- Kids, please.
- I know what you mean.

19:56.863 --> 19:58.780
How old are yours?

19:59.282 --> 20:03.243
Oh. Oh, no. I just teach kids.

20:03.411 --> 20:07.122
I mean, I used to teach kids poetry
before the budget cuts.

20:08.040 --> 20:10.792
So do you come to Ray's games often?

20:10.960 --> 20:13.086
Who, me? Never.

20:13.254 --> 20:15.463
I mean, I did when we were married.

20:15.631 --> 20:17.799
Oh, I was head cheerleader
back in my day.

20:17.967 --> 20:22.470
But no, tonight I figured, "What the heck?"
My husband's working late. I'm an adult.

20:22.638 --> 20:25.473
I'll just go have a great night
with my two lovely kids...

20:25.641 --> 20:27.726
...and watch the Wolves
like we used to, huh?

20:27.894 --> 20:30.729
- Right, kids? Isn't this fun?
DAMON: Mm-hm.

20:30.897 --> 20:32.397
- Hey, hey.
- That's nice.

20:33.441 --> 20:37.193
- How do you know Ray again?
- Oh...

20:37.612 --> 20:39.905
We're friends.

20:40.364 --> 20:42.324
Good friends.

20:43.117 --> 20:46.328
It's complicated, me and Ray.

20:46.495 --> 20:48.455
- How so?
- Whoa!

20:48.623 --> 20:51.082
Nice shot. Go, Wolves.

20:51.250 --> 20:54.544
No, that was for the other team.

20:54.712 --> 20:56.755
We're the white team.
They're the red ones.

20:57.173 --> 20:58.840
Time out.

20:59.008 --> 21:01.343
ANNOUNCER: Time out, Wolves.
MIKE: Bring it in. Let's do it.

21:01.510 --> 21:05.347
This team is not seven points
better than us, right?

21:05.514 --> 21:08.350
All right, all we gotta do is
we gotta make more shots.

21:08.517 --> 21:10.185
It's a simple game, guys.

21:10.353 --> 21:12.520
RAY:
And then she came.

21:12.688 --> 21:16.441
She made me tell her
but I didn't think she'd really show up.

21:19.487 --> 21:21.863
And then suddenly I felt it.

21:22.031 --> 21:24.324
And I wanted to win.

21:25.034 --> 21:27.369
And I wanted to win...

21:27.536 --> 21:30.038
...while she watched.

21:30.206 --> 21:33.208
RAY:
All right, Mike, I got this.

21:33.376 --> 21:36.920
Listen, guys, it's not about shots.

21:37.421 --> 21:40.924
It's not about them. This is about you.

21:41.676 --> 21:45.887
What's inside of you.
What's inside of you.

21:46.263 --> 21:49.891
What do you wanna think tonight when
you replay this game inside your heads...

21:50.059 --> 21:52.560
...with the lights out
and you're trying to sleep?

21:52.728 --> 21:55.355
That you gave it 70 percent?

21:55.523 --> 21:56.731
Or 80 percent?

21:58.859 --> 22:00.610
If we don't give it our all...

22:00.778 --> 22:06.157
...if we don't give it
everything we've got...

22:07.034 --> 22:09.869
...then it don't matter what
the scoreboard says. We lose.

22:10.496 --> 22:15.250
If we believe we're better
than others believe we are...

22:20.214 --> 22:23.341
...if we play with our hearts,
the box score doesn't matter.

22:23.509 --> 22:27.804
The scoreboard doesn't matter.

22:30.683 --> 22:38.940
We win.

22:42.945 --> 22:44.696
"Defense" on three.

22:44.864 --> 22:46.573
All right, guys, one, two, three.

22:46.741 --> 22:49.325
PLAYERS: Defense!
MIKE: Yeah, come on, come on, come on.

22:54.457 --> 22:55.623
[CROWD CHEERING]

22:55.791 --> 22:57.542
All right.

23:02.131 --> 23:03.298
Come on, ref.

23:03.466 --> 23:07.135
Don't let that big freak's zip code affect
the way you ref the game.

23:07.303 --> 23:08.636
Sit down and shut up!

23:08.804 --> 23:10.055
You sit down!

23:10.514 --> 23:12.223
Let's go, Wolves.

23:12.391 --> 23:15.060
CROWD [CHANTING]:
Let's go, Wolves, let's go.

23:15.644 --> 23:16.686
Let's go, Wolves...

23:16.854 --> 23:20.732
RAY: She wanted to see me coach.
I wasn't gonna let her see me lose.

23:20.900 --> 23:22.567
She was gonna get her money's worth.

23:22.735 --> 23:24.319
And this losing streak...

23:24.945 --> 23:27.030
This streak was gonna end.

23:28.657 --> 23:29.949
[CROWD CHEERING]

23:32.286 --> 23:33.661
Trap! Trap!

23:43.130 --> 23:44.923
[WHISTLE BLOWS]

23:52.181 --> 23:54.808
[CROWD GROANS]

24:27.842 --> 24:29.092
[CROWD CHEERING]

24:29.260 --> 24:30.885
No fouls! Don't foul!

24:32.555 --> 24:34.055
[BUZZER SOUNDS]

24:34.223 --> 24:36.850
[CROWD CHEERING]

24:37.351 --> 24:42.063
ANNOUNCER: And the final score is
the Wolves scoring 56 points...

24:42.231 --> 24:45.233
...to the Tomahawks' 55.

25:05.796 --> 25:08.256
- Who is that?
- I don't know.

25:15.931 --> 25:18.183
Good job.

25:18.350 --> 25:20.435
[BAND PLAYING UP-TEMPOED TUNE]

25:20.603 --> 25:23.271
RAY:
That was nice. That's what I like to see.

25:23.439 --> 25:24.606
It was a good game, Mike.

25:24.773 --> 25:27.025
Thanks for keeping it together,
you know, till...

25:27.193 --> 25:32.488
Till what? Until your blond walks in
and turns you around? Who is she?

25:32.740 --> 25:34.699
She's my good-luck charm.

25:35.367 --> 25:38.703
Hey, hold on a second.
Hey. Hey, wait up.

25:39.622 --> 25:40.997
What do you want from me, Ray?

25:41.165 --> 25:45.126
Look, she paid me to come here.
I tried to make her book through you but...

25:45.294 --> 25:47.712
What are you doing here?
You didn't like sports.

25:47.880 --> 25:50.381
You told her where you work.
You told her what you do.

25:50.549 --> 25:53.468
You told her who you are.
You let her into your life.

25:53.636 --> 25:55.803
Are you crazy?
We could go to jail for this.

25:55.971 --> 25:58.014
Will you relax?

25:58.724 --> 26:00.558
I trust her.

26:00.726 --> 26:04.437
You tr... You trust her?

26:07.316 --> 26:10.151
DAMON: Hey. Hey, coach.
- Hey.

26:45.354 --> 26:49.315
JEMMA: That's some leap.
- Yeah.

26:50.359 --> 26:52.360
A long time ago.

26:52.528 --> 26:55.613
You look the same. You look happy.

26:59.910 --> 27:02.120
You wanna go steady?

27:02.663 --> 27:06.207
Well, like you wanna take me to your house
and play Seven Minutes in Heaven?

27:06.375 --> 27:07.792
RAY:
Mm-hm.

27:08.460 --> 27:09.794
You know...

27:10.546 --> 27:12.964
...maybe I won't charge you anymore.

27:13.882 --> 27:16.759
Oh, but then it wouldn't be as fun.
